description:
Add issueCreate GraphQL mutation to linear/mutations.rs:

  mutation IssueCreate($input: IssueCreateInput!) {
    issueCreate(input: $input) {
      success
      issue { id identifier title state { name } priority team { name } }
    }
  }

Required fields: title, teamId
Optional: description, stateId, priority (0-4), assigneeId, labelIds

Function:
  create_issue(token, input: CreateIssueInput) -> Result<Issue>

  pub struct CreateIssueInput {
    pub title: String,
    pub team_id: String,
    pub description: Option<String>,
    pub state_id: Option<String>,
    pub priority: Option<u8>,
    pub assignee_id: Option<String>,
  }

Also need: fetch_teams(token) -> Result<Vec<Team>> to populate team picker (if not already available from cache).

Add notifications query to linear/client.rs (or a new linear/notifications.rs).

GraphQL query:
  query Notifications($first: Int, $after: String) {
    notifications(first: $first, after: $after) {
      nodes {
        id
        type
        readAt
        createdAt
        updatedAt
        ... on IssueNotification {
          issue { identifier title state { name } priority team { name } }
          actor { name }
        }
      }
      pageInfo { hasNextPage endCursor }
    }
  }

Types needed:
  Notification { id, type_, read_at: Option<String>, created_at, updated_at, issue: Option<Issue>, actor: Option<String> }

Function: fetch_notifications(token, first: usize) -> Result<Vec<Notification>>

Note: 'type' is a reserved keyword in Rust -- use type_ or notification_type.

Add GraphQL mutations to linear/client.rs (or a new linear/mutations.rs):

issueUpdate mutation covers all three fields in one call:
  mutation IssueUpdate($id: String!, $input: IssueUpdateInput!) {
    issueUpdate(id: $id, input: $input) {
      success
      issue { id identifier title state { name } priority assignee { name } }
    }
  }

Functions to expose:
  update_issue_state(token, id, state_id) -> Result<Issue>
  update_issue_priority(token, id, priority: u8) -> Result<Issue>
  update_issue_assignee(token, id, assignee_id: Option<String>) -> Result<Issue>

Also need a helper to fetch available workflow states for a team:
  fetch_workflow_states(token, team_id) -> Result<Vec<WorkflowState>>
  WorkflowState { id: String, name: String, type_: String }

State IDs are UUIDs -- the TUI needs to fetch them once and cache in SQLite (or in-memory for the session).

Add a new GraphQL query to linear/client.rs (or issues/detail.rs) that fetches a single issue by ID with:
  - description (markdown body text)
  - comments { nodes { body, createdAt, user { name } } }
  - Full state, assignee, priority, team, labels

New types needed in linear/types.rs:
  IssueDetail { ...existing fields..., description: Option<String>, comments: Vec<Comment> }
  Comment { body: String, created_at: String, author: String }

Function signature: fetch_issue_detail(token, id) -> Result<IssueDetail>
